  "title": "Quality Assurance Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Job Objectives:<br />1. To ensure all products produced are of highest quality and meet or exceed customer requirements.</p><p>2. To ensure all activities perform in accordance to AS9100 standard and in line with the company Quality Policy<br /><br />3.Responsible to establish and revise ballon drawing, inspection plan and report<br /></p><p>Job Responsibilities:<br /></p><p>1. Responsible to establish and revise ballon drawing, inspection plan and report</p><p>2.  Constantly improve the quality level thru developing effective inspection plan, method and upgrading inspection skill.</p><p>3. Manage inspection activities and resources to provide the necessary support to ensure smooth manufacturing operation.</p><p>4. Generate monthly/weekly Quality Reports (IQA, NCR, CAR, LAR and customer complaint, etc.) and updates the management on quality performance regularly.</p><p>5. Train, certify and requalify QA Personnel.</p><p>6. Handle FA inspection package and submit to customer (IPR, COC, PQP, etc)</p><p>7. Handle customer quality issues and champion corrective action plan to customer.</p><p>8. Work with Quality System Engineer to ensure quality system is effective implemented and maintained.</p><p>9. In charge of maintaining quality records and QA archiving room activities.</p><p>10. Enforce safety standard and maintain good housekeeping practise at QA related area.</p><p>11. As internal auditor to audit respective area and liaise with customer on audit related as auditee.</p><p>12. Manage inspection activities and resources to provide the necessary support to ensure smooth QA operation at CMM.</p><p>13. Responsible to create, establish and revised CMM program for CMM inspection. Get approval CMM PCO and submit to doc control.</p><p>14. Manage inspection activities and resources to provide the necessary support to ensure smooth QA operation at CMM</p><p>15. Perform regular analysis on CMM in rectifying machine errors in order to improve efficiency and to reduce machine downtime.</p>",
